OL,3,CUK Government no longer 'global
OL,4,Ccharity', aid minister to tell MPs
OL,6,FShe will say: "We need to support
OL,7,Fother countries' systems where this is
OL,8,Fwhat they want, so they can educate
OL,9,Ftheir children, reform their own
OL,10,Fhealthcare systems and grow their
OL,11,Feconomies in ways which last.
OL,13,F"And, ultimately, exit the need for
OL,14,Faid.
OL,16,F"With less to spend, we have no
OL,17,Fchoice. Biggest impact and biggest
OL,18,Fspend aren't always the same thing."
